The paper deals with the segmentation of liver ablation zones from CT scans, which is a task commonly addressed in computer vision (cs.CV) and medical imaging (cs.MED) research. The proposed method uses a graph-based approach, which involves optimization and machine learning techniques, making it relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also discusses the quantitative evaluation of the proposed method, which involves statistical analysis and similarity metrics, making it relevant to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
